# Documentation Questions

## What Is an Inventory?

### Answer

An Inventory is a file that contains the list of managed nodes and connection information. It allows Ansible to identify which servers should receive automation tasks.

---

## Why Use Groups?

### Answer

Groups allow multiple servers with similar roles to be managed together.

Example:

```ini
[web]
web-server

[app]
app-server
```

Commands can target an entire group:

```bash
ansible web -m ping
```

instead of targeting individual servers.

---

## What Is the Purpose of `[all:vars]`?

### Answer

`[all:vars]` defines variables that apply to every host in the inventory.

Example:

```ini
[all:vars]
ansible_user=ec2-user
ansible_ssh_private_key_file=/home/malathi/.ssh/ansible-lab.pem
```

This eliminates repetitive connection parameters.

